REG_0x01.Description_StringValue: Software reset. This bit is self clearing.
REG_0x01.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = Reset all registers to their reset values

REG_0x02.Description_StringValue:
The analog supply selection from either the internal regulator supply 
or the external AREG supply.
REG_0x02.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = External 1.8-V AREG supply 
(use this setting when AVDD is 1.8V and short AREG with AVDD)
REG_0x02.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Internally generated 1.8-V AREG supply 
using an on-chip regulator (use this setting when AVDD is 3.3 V)

REG_0x02.Description_StringValue:
The duration of the quick-charge for the VREF external capacitor is 
set using an internal series impedance of 200 Ω.

REG_0x02.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = I2C broadcast mode enabled; the I2C slave address is 
fixed at 1001 100
1d = Device is not in sleep mode

REG_0x07.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = 16 bits (Recommended this setting to be used with 10-kΩ
or 20-kΩ input impedance configuration
0d = Default polarity as per standard protocol
REG_0x07.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = Inverted polarity with respect to standard protocol

REG_0x07.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = Default polarity as per standard protocol
REG_0x07.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = Inverted polarity with respect to standard protocol

REG_0x07.Description_StringValue:
ASI data output (on the primary and secondary data pin)
transmit edge
REG_0x07.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = Default edge as per the protocol configuration setting 
in bit 2(BCLK_POL)
REG_0x07.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Inverted following edge (half cycle delay) with respect 
to the default edge setting

REG_0x07.Description_StringValue:
ASI data output (on the primary and secondary data pin)
for any unused cycles
REG_0x07.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = Always use Hi-Z for unused cycles

REG_0x08.Description_StringValue: ASI data output (on the primary and secondary data pin) for LSB transmissions.
REG_0x08.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = Transmit the LSB for a full cycle
REG_0x08.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Transmit the LSB for the first half cycle and Hi-Z
for the second half cycle

REG_0x08.Description_StringValue: ASI data output (on the primary and secondary data pin) bus keeper.
REG_0x08.RadioButton_2_Option:
2d = Bus keeper is enabled during LSB transmissions only
for one cycle
REG_0x08.RadioButton_3_Option:
3d = Bus keeper is enabled during LSB transmissions only
for one and half cycles

REG_0x08.Description_StringValue: ASI data MSB slot 0 offset (on the primary and secondary data pin).
REG_0x08.Result_Description_StringValue: ASI data MSB location has no offset and is as per standard protocol

REG_0x09.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = All devices are connected in the common ASI bus
REG_0x09.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d =All devices are daisy-chained for the ASI bus.
This is supported only if ASI input mixing is disabled,
refer register 10 for details on ASI input mixing feature.

REG_0x09.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = Enable auto resume after bus error recovery
REG_0x09.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Disable auto resume after bus error recovery and remain
powered down until the host configures the device

REG_0x0A.Description_StringValue: ASI input (from GPIx or GPIO) mixing selection with channel data.
REG_0x0A.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Channel 1 and channel 2 output data mixed with 
ASI input data on channel 1 (slot 0)
REG_0x0A.RadioButton_2_Option:
2d = Channel 1 and channel 2 output data mixed with 
ASI input data on channel 2 (slot 1)
REG_0x0A.RadioButton_3_Option:
3d = Mixed both channel data with ASI input data independently.
Mixed asi_in_ch_1 with channel 1 output data and similarly
mix asi_in_ch_2 with channel 2 output data

REG_0x0A.Description_StringValue: ASI input data gain selection before mixing to channel data.
Invert ASI input data before mixing to channel data.
REG_0x0A.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = No inversion done for ASI input data
REG_0x0A.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = ASI input data inverted before mixing with channel data

REG_0x0B.Result_Description_StringValue: TDM is slot %d or I2S, LJ is right slot %d

REG_0x0C.Result_Description_StringValue: TDM is slot %d or I2S, LJ is right slot %d

REG_0x0D.Result_Description_StringValue: TDM is slot %d or I2S, LJ is right slot %d

REG_0x0E.Result_Description_StringValue: TDM is slot %d or I2S, LJ is right slot %d

REG_0x13.Description_StringValue: ASI master or slave configuration register setting.
REG_0x13.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = Device is in slave mode (both BCLK and FSYNC are
inputs to the device)
REG_0x13.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Device is in master mode (both BCLK and FSYNC are
generated from the device)

REG_0x13.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = Auto clock configuration is enabled (all internal clock 
divider and PLL configurations are auto derived)
REG_0x13.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Auto clock configuration is disabled (custom mode and
device GUI must be used for the device configuration settings)

REG_0x13.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = PLL is enabled in auto clock configuration
REG_0x13.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = PLL is disabled in auto clock configuration

REG_0x13.Description_StringValue: BCLK and FSYNC clock gate(valid when the device is in master mode).
REG_0x13.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = Do not gate BCLK and FSYNC
REG_0x13.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Force gate BCLK and FSYNC when being transmitted from
the device in master mode

REG_0x13.Description_StringValue: Sample rate setting (valid when the device is in master mode).
REG_0x13.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = fS is a multiple (or submultiple) of 48 kHz
REG_0x13.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = fS is a multiple (or submultiple) of 44.1 kHz

REG_0x13.Description_StringValue:
These bits select the MCLK (GPIO or GPIx) frequency for the PLL
source clock input (valid when the device is in master mode
and MCLK_FREQ_SEL_MODE = 0).

REG_0x14.Description_StringValue:
Programmed sample rate of the ASI bus (not used when the device
is configured in slave mode auto clock configuration).

Programmed BCLK to FSYNC frequency ratio of the ASI bus 
(not used when the device is configured in slave mode
auto clock configuration).

REG_0x15.Description_StringValue: Detected sample rate of the ASI bus.
Detected BCLK to FSYNC frequency ratio of the ASI bus.

REG_0x16.Description_StringValue:
Audio root clock source setting when the device is configured with
the PLL disabled in the auto clock configuration for
slave mode (AUTO_MODE_PLL_DIS = 1).
REG_0x16.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = BCLK is used as the audio root clock sourc
REG_0x16.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = MCLK (GPIO or GPIx) is used as the audio root clock source
(the MCLK to FSYNC ratio is as per MCLK_RATIO_SEL setting)

REG_0x16.Description_StringValue:
Master mode MCLK (GPIO or GPIx) frequency selection mode
(valid when the device is in auto clock configuration).
REG_0x16.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = MCLK frequency is based on the MCLK_FREQ_SEL (P0_R19)
configuration
REG_0x16.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = MCLK frequency is specified as a multiple of FSYNC in the
MCLK_RATIO_SEL (P0_R22) configuration

REG_0x16.Description_StringValue:
These bits select the MCLK (GPIO or GPIx) to FSYNC ratio for
master mode or when MCLK is used as the audio
root clock source in slave mode.

Invert BCLK polarity only for FSYNC generation in master mode
configuration.
REG_0x16.RadioButton_0_Option: 0d = Do not invert BCLK polarity for FSYNC generation
REG_0x16.RadioButton_1_Option: 1d = Invert BCLK polarity for FSYNC generation

REG_0x1F.RadioButton_3_Option:
3d = PDMCLK is 5.6448 MHz or 6.144 MHz
(applicable only for PDM channel 1 and 2)

REG_0x20.Description_StringValue: PDMCLK latching edge used for channel 1 and channel 2 data.
REG_0x20.RadioButton_0_Option:
0d = Channel 1 data are latched on the negative edge, channel 2
data are latched on the positive edge
REG_0x20.RadioButton_1_Option:
1d = Channel 1 data are latched on the positive edge, channel 2
data are latched on the negative edge
